Narrative:
On February [XXX], 2025 at 1:32 AM PT a Waymo Autonomous Vehicle ("Waymo AV") operating in Brisbane, California was in a collision involving a hand truck dolly on [XXX] near [XXX].
The Waymo AV was traveling southbound on [XXX] in the leftmost lane of two southbound lanes when an oncoming vehicle in the northbound lane struck a hand truck dolly, which was then projected from the northbound lane through the median lane and into the southbound lane occupied by the Waymo AV. The front of the Waymo AV then made contact with the hand truck dolly, which became lodged at the front of the Waymo AV. At the time of the impact, the Waymo AV's Level 4 ADS was engaged in autonomous mode. The Waymo AV and the hand truck dolly sustained damage.
Waymo is reporting this crash under Request No. 1 of Standing General Order 2021-01 because a vehicle involved was towed away. Waymo may supplement or correct its reporting with additional information as it may become available.

On January [XXX], 2025 at 6:42 AM PT a Waymo Autonomous Vehicle (Waymo AV) operating in San Francisco, California was in a collision involving a passenger car on [XXX] near [XXX].
The Waymo AV was proceeding south on [XXX] when a passenger car in front of the Waymo AV entered the two-way center turn lane on its left. As the Waymo AV neared the passenger car, the passenger car began to maneuver out of the center turn lane and re-enter the singular lane of [XXX]. The passenger side of the passenger car then made contact with the driver side of the Waymo AV. At the time of the impact, the Waymo AVs Level 4 ADS was engaged in autonomous mode. Both vehicles sustained damage.
Waymo is reporting this crash under Request No. 1 of Standing General Order 2021-01 because a vehicle involved was towed away. Waymo may supplement or correct its reporting with additional information as it may become available.

On Thursday, November [XXX], 2024 at 11:04 CST, a Waymo Autonomous Vehicle ("Waymo AV") operating in Austin, Texas was in a collision involving a raised concrete curb in a parking lot on [XXX] near [XXX].
The Waymo AV was proceeding through a parking lot on [XXX] near [XXX] in autonomous mode when it encountered a passenger car parked outside the marked parking spaces occupying a portion of the parking lot apparently intended for ingress and egress from the lot rather than parking.  The AV came to a stop, and shortly thereafter the test driver assumed manual control of the AV.  The test driver reversed slightly and then proceeded through a vacant marked parking space to pass around the parked passenger car, and as the AV crossed through the vacant parking space it made contact with a raised concrete curb.
At the time of the impact, the Waymo AV's Level 4 ADS was not engaged and a test driver was operating the Waymo AV in manual.  This is a duplicate of NHTSA Report ID: 30270-9232-1.

Narrative:
**1-Day Incident Report 5/25/2024**
Customer contacted Kia Customer Care (KCC) to report an incident involving his 2023MY Kia Sportage. Specifically, the customer called to thank Kia "for saving [REDACTED, MAY CONTAIN CONFIDENTIAL BUSINESS INFORMATION] life." Customer explained he was in a head-on collision when a drunk driver suddenly veered into his lane.  Customer reported he suffered "cuts, bumps & bruises" and stated he "believes that [REDACTED, MAY CONTAIN CONFIDENTIAL BUSINESS INFORMATION] lack of injuries is due to the plethora of safety features my Sportage had."  KCC subsequently contacted the customer to obtain additional details regarding the incident.  Customer stated that he was driving on a two-lane highway around 3AM, with cruise control engaged, when the car he was following veered into a ditch and a drunk driver veered into his lane. Customer did not see the drunk driver until the last second and as a result did not have time react.  When asked by KCC, the customer responded that Highway Driving Assist (HDA) was not engaged, but that his Smart Cruise Control and Lane Following Assist were engaged at the time of the incident.  The customer reported that the Sportage's airbags deployed, both the customer and driver of the other vehicle (unclear if the drunk driver or the driver of the vehicle that veered into the ditch) were transported to the hospital and that the Sportage was towed. Customer stated he was not asking anything from Kia and that he had called only to share his appreciation. 
This incident is being reported as precautionary measure since the incident meets the requirements under the SGO.  However, based on the description of the incident provided by the customer, the incident was not caused by a failure and/or disengagement of smart cruise control and/or LFA.
**10-Day Update 6/3/2024**
No additional information to be provided as the 1-Day was reported as a precautionary measure and submitting this 10-Day Update per the reporting requirements under the SGO.

On May [XXX], 2024 at 12:58 AM PT a Waymo Autonomous Vehicle ("Waymo AV") operating in Los Angeles, CA was in a collision involving a passenger car on eastbound [XXX] between [XXX] and [XXX]. 
The Waymo AV was traveling with a test driver present behind a box truck in the number 3 lane of eastbound [XXX] near the [XXX] when a passenger car traveling at a high rate of speed approached the Waymo AV from behind. The passenger car partially entered the number 2 lane as the front right corner of the passenger car made contact with the rear left corner of the Waymo AV. The passenger car then made contact with the center median and came to a stop. The Waymo AV was transitioned into manual mode, and the test driver stopped the Waymo AV to the right-hand shoulder. At the time of the impact, the Waymo AV's Level 4 ADS was engaged in autonomous mode, and a test driver was present (in the driver's seating position). Both vehicles sustained damage.
Waymo is reporting this crash under Request No. 1 of Standing General Order 2021-01 because an individual involved was transported from the scene to a hospital for medical treatment, a vehicle involved was towed away, and an airbag deployed. Waymo may supplement or correct its reporting with additional information as it may become available.
